cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with radio networks and broadcast algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the cost of sending, listening, and jamming on different channels. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for broadcast. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with an adversary trying to disrupt a system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an efficient algorithm for message dissemination.
